{
  "body": "See\nhttps://docs.perl6.org/routine/split\nhttps://github.com/perl6/roast/blob/master/S32-str/split-simple.t#L44-L45\n\nIn other languages such as Scala, Python, Perl 5, and so on, specifying the negative LIMIT as the argument of the split routine means \"split as much as possible\".\nHowever, unlike other languages, Perl 6 returns empty result when specifying the negative LIMIT.\n\nI think the above situation should be documented and exampled.\n",
